Gulf Stocks: Arabtec Holding, Burgan Bank, Qatar Islamic Bank

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-05-25T08:07:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/gulf-stocks-arabtec-holding-burgan-bank-qatar-islamic-bank.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  declined for a
fifth day, losing 0.8 percent to 1,532.69 at 11:42 a.m. in
Dubai.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  and Kuwait’s gauge
decreased 0.2 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   dropped as much as 2.3
percent to 1.26 dirhams, before trading at 1.28 dirhams. The
biggest construction company in the United Arab Emirates by
market value was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at EFG-Hermes
Holding SAE with a 12-month price estimate of 1.46 dirhams a
share.        Burgan Bank (BURG)  SAK advanced the most in almost a
month, rising 2 percent to 510 fils. The Kuwaiti lender was
started with a “neutral” recommendation at Goldman Sachs Group
Inc. and assigned a 24-month price estimate of 0.58 dinar.        Qatar Islamic Bank (QIBK)   decreased 1 percent to 78.4
riyals. The Persian Gulf country’s biggest Shariah-compliant
lender was lowered to “hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank AG
with a 12-month share price estimate of 97 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  